@startuml component-native-pdf-planned
'' ============================================================================
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this is a CROSS-PROCESS component diagram with
'' a security/IPC seam, where the entire feature is «planned». PlantUML's
'' component stereotype styling (the shared <<planned>> dashed-grey skin defined
'' in _vv-theme.iuml) lets us mark not-yet-built parts uniformly while keeping
'' the already-built process frames solid, and color the IPC arrows amber per
'' the palette. Mermaid cannot apply a reusable "planned" stereotype skin.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Native PDF (Forthcoming / «planned») — a BrowserView positioned over the active tab

rectangle "Electron MAIN process" as MAIN #3A5BA0 {
  component "main.service\n(existing)" as SVC #3A5BA0
  component "PdfService" as PDF <<planned>>
  component "BrowserView\nnavigated to file://…pdf\n(Chromium PDF viewer)" as BV <<planned>>
  component "chokidar watcher\n(existing — reused)" as WATCH #9F8766
}

rectangle "preload (contextBridge seam)" as PRE #B1951D {
  component "window.vv.pdfBounds(rect)\nwindow.vv.onPdfReload(cb)" as BRIDGE <<planned>>
}

rectangle "Electron RENDERER (Chromium)" as REND #2D9574 {
  component "content-view\nStrategy (existing)" as CV #2D9574
  component "pdf placeholder div\n(measured each layout)" as PH <<planned>>
}

CV -[#B1951D,dashed,thickness=2]-> BRIDGE : (1) report placeholder bounds\n(getBoundingClientRect) over IPC
BRIDGE -[#B1951D,dashed,thickness=2]-> PDF  : (2) {x,y,w,h}
PDF -[#999999,dashed,thickness=2]-> BV      : (3) setBounds(rect)\n+ attach over the window
WATCH -[#9F8766,dashed,thickness=2]-> PDF   : (4) file change →\nBV.webContents.reload()
PDF -[#B1951D,dashed,thickness=2]-> BRIDGE  : (5) onPdfReload notify
PH .[#999999,dashed]. BV : visually occupies\nthe same rectangle

note bottom of REND
  The renderer keeps the **tab/scroll/find** state in app-db; the BrowserView is
  a separate native surface owned by MAIN, kept aligned to the placeholder by IPC
  bounds messages. Live-refresh reuses the **same chokidar watcher per open path**
  as Markdown — only the action (reload the BrowserView) differs.
end note

legend right
  |= color/style |= concept |
  | <#3A5BA0> | MAIN process (Node IO) — solid = existing |
  | <#B1951D> | IPC seam (contextBridge) — all IPC arrows amber |
  | <#2D9574> | renderer (Chromium UI) — solid = existing |
  | <#9F8766> | filesystem watcher (reused) |
  | dashed grey <<planned>> | NOT yet built (Forthcoming) |
endlegend
@enduml
